1.format SDcard http://qdosmsq.dunbar-it.co.uk/blog/2013/06/noobs-for-raspberry-pi/
  fdisk /dev/mmcblk0
  d p
  mkfs.vfat /dev/mmcblk0
  mkfs.vfat /dev/mmcblk0p1
  mkfs.vfat /dev/mmcblk0p2
  Use disks App  
2.Download RASPBIAN STRETCH WITH DESKTOP .zip  https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/raspbian/
3.WRITING AN IMAGE TO THE SD CARD https://etcher.io/
4.Creat ssh file in boot right click >> new >>document >> ssh
  if error
  ##cd /media/mmxxx
  cd /media/boot
  touch ssh
5.connect Rasperry--router
6.Check RassberryPI IP by sign in router (192.168.1.1) or use application
7.terminal ssh pi@pi_ip
8.install VNC
  sudo apt-get update
  sudo apt-get upgrade
  sudo apt-get install tightvncserver
  sudo apt-get install xrdp
   vncserver :1
9. sudo raspi-config >> interfacing option > vnc > enable
10.install VNC on ubuntu

